CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 14, 1958, pg. B6, reads: "SMILING TEACHERS - Among Pitt's new holders of Master of Education Degrees are, left to right, Margie Sue Walker of Aliquippa; Florence Irby Queen of Wilmerding; Helen L. George of Cleveland, Ohio; Everett Superior Williams of Clairton; and William Edward Green of Pittsburgh."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Margie Sue Walker, Florence Irby Queen, Helen L. George, Everett Superior Williams, and William Edward Green wearing dark caps and gowns, and light colored stoles, after receiving Master of Education Degrees, at University of Pittsburgh graduation
